caption: Staff was nice! Personally, the food to me wasn’t great. Alfredo wasn’t thick or creamy, chicken was good on the ends but the middle seemed chewy. My friend liked his chicken parm. The bread sticks were bland to me.
Absolutely a great place.  Sit up top, great view.

Normally I get Mufalattas from the Central Grocery, I got delayed and couldn't make it before they closed. Simply ordered 3 Mufalattas to go. Best neighborhood restaurant in the French Quarter

The crab cakes here were one of the best things that I ate during our week stay in New Orleans. Andy was very kind. The muffeleta with Frank's signature hot sauce was amazing after enjoying a few drinks.

Good food but we got the bill and it seemed steep.  We paid, and tipped. Great service. Had BBQ Shrimp and Shrimp Poboy.
A bit pricey, but overall Outstanding food and service. Be prepared to take a to-go box.

The waitress was very rude, we asked for a larger table, she had a fit.  She over charged us for things we didn't order, my shrimp was horrible... once the food came  she gave us our bill and we didn't see her again. Great way to spend $90 to be treated horrible.
The best seafood platter & great service ! Flavor was on point !

The service and the food are both great at Frank's. Andy made sure we had an experience while we visited, not just a meal. The house made marinara is fresh and flavorful. The barbecue shrimp we huge and the sauce was really unique. Definitely recommend!

We had such a terrible experience here. The gumbo that was suppose to be rated #1 was sour and very watery. The red beans and rice had no rice and it also very nasty. Paid $100 dollars for 4  shrimp po'boys that weren't the best, it was a good place to visit just could have been better.

Paid 200$ for the most disgusting food in my life. We got 4 VIRGIN drinks that they were 25$ a piece and the tasted like SOAP! On the menu it says party of 5 people and we charge gratuity. Food and people were awesome!

Worst $80 ever spend! The crab stuffed mushrooms were greasy, oily, gooey and salty. It was like squishy stuffing plopped on top of 4 mushrooms and tasted terrible. We also ordered oysters that I am pretty sure weren't properly cleaned before being battered and deep fried to hell. The calamari appetizer was the only thing worth eating but still heavily breaded and fried. Would not recommend!
I love Franks! Great Italian food. Service is really great!
Good food, service is okay, friendly place. A little pricey, but you get a good meal.
Great muffelata
Frank's is a wonderful place.  Great food at a fair price.  Come hungry and leave happy.  I ate here twice and loved it both times.
First time visiting the city, I tried many foods in different places without a doubt they make the best Gumbo you can find delicious

Found ourselves here during pandemic,  terrific food and full bar and wonderful conversations with staff. My companion can't eat seafood, so he had chicken parmigiana that he said was amazing and I had an oyster po'boy that was exactly what I had hoped to find.

The lady asked if my bf wanted garlic bread with his chicken parmesean but didn't bother telling us that it was extra. Then she added her tip to the ticket and decided not deserve any of it. After we got done eating we saw her outside smoking a cigarette and she went back in and went straight to another table she was serving. Did not wash her hands. Worse experience I have ever had in new orleans and we come here often.
Just happened to be in town for business and was looking for a cozy restaurant and just happened to stumble upon this gem! The food was great and the service was spectacular!
love their olive salad

We were there on a Saturday night on the balcony and our waiter was attentive and made our dining experience so enjoyable. Recommend this place highly if you are going to be in the area. We had garlic bread app, caeser salad, mussels Marinara pasta and the stuffed ricotta ravioli. SO GOOD!!!!

Was curious about grabbing some food to go, and when i tried to ask one of the employees about it he was too busy trying to fight honeless people and told me to f off. It was very unprofessional and i pass by the restaurant every day and my curiousity for this restaurant has turned into disgust.
Not the best food but lively fun characters run/own it

Would be zero stars.  It’s too expensive. They were gouging prices on tourists and pushing 18% tips even though the food was cold, old from the morning, and just over all bad.

Go somewhere else!  I had a bowl of seafood gumbo.  Well this seafood gumbo had exactly 4 small shrimp and several shells from the shrimp.  Nothing else!  NOTHING!! No crab, no fish, no sausage NOTHING!!! For $9.95!!  Never again.  Go to Mothers.  Great place.
Excellent food and service. Owners care about customers experience.

We ate at Frank’s for lunch on my husband’s Birthday this past weekend. I am so glad Joey came out on the sidewalk to invite us in! Our party of seven was not disappointed! We all loved our meals! Especially the Muffuletta Sandwich! Everything we ordered was amazing! Kathy, our waitress never let our Dixie Beers get too empty! She was very attentive! This is a great little place and we highly recommend it!
Employee made racial comment to us when viewing the menu! Will never eat there because of that!

I guess we ordered wrong?  We were craving pasta so I asked what vegetables were in their Fettuccine Prima Vera.  The waitress stuck her head in the kitchen to ask and the cook literally said "I don't know, lemme see what we've got in the freezer."  Sure enough, a few minutes later he comes walking through the dining room with a huge bag of frozen broccoli and says "how about broccoli?"   About 10 minutes later I was served overcooked dried pasta with huge chunks of frozen broccoli (mostly stems) and what I'm fairly certain was a a jar of Ragu al Fredo sauce.  It was barely edible and cost me $28!   Maybe I should have ordered a Po Boy, but its supposedly an Italian Restaurant - really?

To be honest, their food was great. We got an array of items at the table and everyone around seemed to love the food. But let me tell you how insanely awkward it is to be in a dining room enjoying your meal while the staff go at it screaming and cussing each other. So bad they'd openly bash each other while speaking with us. If you're going to have a war, at least do it in the kitchen away from your guests. Be respectful of each other. Business vs personal. Displays today were SUPER personal. I've seen people fired for less.

We entered excited to eat some Italian food. Now let me start by saying I'm from Jersey and went with my two Italian friends from Staten island. With that being said we know our sicilian dishes. The food was mediocre, it definitely needed more garlic and seasonings. But the food was not really the issue,  it was the service. Being from up north we are accustom to courteous  service, the waitress, "Tammy", was rude, snappy and annoyed with our every question and request. It took everything in us not to walk out. She did seem busy but there was no need for her behavior. She really made our experience at this establishment an unpleasant one.
VERY expensive and was forced to pay an 18% tip w/o choice. The food was not worth the price!

This place is one of the worst to stop by. I’m going to make this short by saying that owner and waitress were arguing in front of us for 16 dollars. Very unprofessional ghetto people to do such a thing in front of guests. But the worst part was not only did that happened but I ordered chicken parmigiana and it had a hair in between the mozzarella. How nasty is that. Right away we asked for the check and left. If I could give this place 0 stars I would.
This place is consistently excellent. I’ve been several times while visiting New Orleans and I’m always very happy with their muffuletta and stuffed mushrooms.
Best muffaletta I've ever eaten

It’s been here since the 60’s and the reason is simple . Real Italian cuisine created by real Italian family. Great service to the table always by local service industry folks . This is an authentic New Orleans French Quarter Icon . Give this place a try , they don’t make them like this anymore .
Joey is the best! Best muffuletta in New Orleans!

By far the absolute best muffelatta in all of New Orleans!! And a thank you to Joey who's always there to greet you at the door, we would have never stopped if he hadn't made us feel so welcome and told how good the food was. Thanks Joey and we'll definitely be back!!

Frequent Nola visitor and this restaurant definitely passes the test. Have the "Taste of New Orleans". One of the best gumbos and jambalayas I've had yet. The fettuccine is delicious if you want a typical pasta dish. Their Fettuccini sauce is much better the most I've tried anywhere. The service here is incredible. Very attentive and friendly. Even the coffee is decent which is hard for me to find even in New York (but I've found Nola to have many good coffee joints). I think y'all would really enjoy your meal here. The little old man out front is what convinced me to try this place. This is not your typical Italiano Restaurante.
The food was ok but the waitress was in a foul mood and so were the other 2 Skip it
Food prices were reasonable, unfortunately after they added 18% gratuity for a party of 2 and their drink "special" was a $12 hurricane, our total was over $100.

I stopped for a to-go Muffaletta. I got mine heated. They toast the sandwich open-faced then add the olive and pepper Muffaletta relish, which is a lot like a mild giardiniera with olives. By the time I actually got it to my place a few blocks away, it had cooked, of course, but it was delicious. I had stopped in Central Grocery a couple days earlier, near closing time, and it reeked. It didn't smell like any Italian deli I'd ever been in, so I resolved to get my Muffaletta fix somewhere else.  Frank's is very close by and I'm glad I got mine there.  Knocked off one star for the surley staff.

This place is amazing. I love the worker named andy. He was really funny.

Muffuletta was way too greasy. Veggie Po-Boy was olives, lettuce, tomato, and pickles. Can’t believe they charged $12 for a sandwich with nothing on it.

Giving 3 stars, because sitting on the balcony was really great. Crab cakes were delicious! Crab stuffed mushrooms were also great.  The gumbo was not good. Prices were too high, in my opinion. The staff seemed nervous/on edge. We were treated kindly by waitresses. Not sure if they are treated poorly by management, or what.  Wasn't the cleanest place in town, felt very old school New Orleans.  If you are only going to be eating at a couple places- skip this one. If you are in town for a while, and plan on going to many restaurants- wont hurt to stop in.

We were starving and in the long line for a muffaletta at Central Grocery when the man outside Frank's invited us in. Since we were hungry and there was no line, we decided to take a chance. Everyone talls about the brusqueness of the waitress, but I've got in laws from NY so it didnt seem any different than that. The muffaletta is HUGE. My husband I split  a whole and my teen daughter  got a half. In reality,  all three of us could have split  a whole.  I did notice that the 18% gratuity was added on, but after reading reviews I was prepared for that. I figured it's a touristy spot so whatever.  Muffaletta was very good!

We were wandering in the French quarter looking for a place to eat. Joey coaxed us to come inside and try some of Franks good cooking. We sat upstairs on the balcony and was able to people watch and hear good music from the surrounding bars. The food was ok. Joey who works the door was a nice man to meet.

My son's shrimp poboy was mediocre. He said the bread was the best part of it. My daughter in law had a shrimp dish. The shrimp were anything but fresh. Perfect :)
Great food and great balcony to people watch. Extensive menu.  Despite other claims, Frank's has the best muffuletta in New Orleans.

Service was ok, food was terrible. There was only one small table of four occupied while we were there and we had a party of 7. It took forever to get our food and when we did it was barely warm. And the prices were expensive considering the quality of the food. I wouldn’t and don’t recommend this place.
The food was so good. Big portions so we had some tasty leftovers for later. Missy was our server and was the best. Very attentive and personable. We will be back.
View was great, food was meh.

Frank's promised a lot but was pretty average. A very traditional old fashioned interior which in today's terms would be described as shabby chic.  The menu was simple and so was the food. A little too simple to be honest. Very bland and unimaginative. Not bad enough for 2 stars but not really good enough for 3.
The food is overpriced and mediocre. The service is basically non existent and with a party of 2 I was not expecting them to add 18% gratuity . Yall I'm a local and I urge you go to oceana or landrys

This place is a no frills place, with amazing food! My vegetarian wife and I decided to eat here since the menu was accommodating for us both! I got a house special shrimp and pasta dish and it was outstanding! Service was great, never overbearing and I their suggestions were not for the top dollar menu prices and came from what seemed as pretty genuine personal favorites. We also read that the tiramisu desert here was supposedly a local favorite. Well the wife and I split one and IT WAS SERIOUSLY THE BEST TIRAMISU WE BOTH HAVE EVER HAD! I almost ordered another but we were both stuffed! We will definitely return to at least have that amazing tiramisu again!
Enjoyed the atmosphere & flavor   the red beans and rice rocked.

Welcoming environment,  Great service . The food is fantastic and reasonably priced.

Great food and service. My waiter Andy was the most honest and nicest waiter I have ever had however the other waitress, Cathy, was very loud and rude to other employees.

The server was rude and pushy.  Wouldn't give us time to enjoy our drinks and appetizer.  The calamari was the worst calamari I have ever tasted. The only good thing about this place was their bloody Mary's that were were $11 with the house vodka.

We were walking around the French Quarter on a very hot day in NOLA a couple days ago. I was hungry and overheated so my husband and I were desperate to find a restaurant that wasn’t so crowded. The manager or owner? Of Frank’s restaurant was standing outside trying to get people to come in. That should have been red flag number one, but we were desperate so we went in. It was air conditioned and felt amazing. But then, our waitress was really lacking in the customer service department. I don’t even remember her name but she didn’t smile once, and almost acted like we were wasting her time. Anytime she would set something on our table she’d set it down and kind of heavily sigh and say “here you go” and walk away without asking if we needed anything or even giving us a glance. It was weird. I had the shrimp po’boy. And honestly it wasn’t half bad, I’d order it again. My husband had the spaghetti and meatballs and said it wasn’t good. Also... $4.50 for a side of fries which weren’t seasoned or salted at all, and $4.50 for a side of garlic bread. In all, we spent $50 on a very mediocre lunch and dining experience and we left pretty unsatisfied. I also forgot to mention another employee was speaking to someone on the phone very loudly for all to hear and was being really rude to whoever was on the other line (it sounded like a customer but can’t say for sure) he was describing the ingredients for one of their dishes and then proceeded to call whoever it was a “dumbass” and was visibly getting frustrated. It was uncomfortable. We had our 10 month old infant with us so would have appreciated a better environment and better service but what can you do i guess. For our first real dining experience in NOLA it was disappointing.

Food was bland to say the least shrimp was terrible first time I've ever had bad shrimp that was not cleaned and I could taste it rest of the food had no taste at all especially for the price that was paid I can say the fries where good and our server and cook that came out to help her where GREAT! Also the view on the roof was also pleasant!

Went for my birthday and it was wonderful.  The food was amazing and the staff were so friendly.  I felt like family.  Kathy made me the best Hurricane I have ever had.  In fact the food and atmosphere was so great I’m already planning my return just to have dinner at the restaurant.

Excellent food.  No frills, solid service,  and Kathy truly makes the best darn White Russian I'd ever had!!! Kathy gave me her secret recipe, but I promised I wouldn't tell. The corn and crab chowder is phenomenal and my husband loved the marinara with perfectly cooked pasta,  my husband would know,  he's a big foodie!  We're only in town for 5 days, with such a vast variety of fabulous food in New Orleans, we had still chosen to eat here, twice!! I haven't read other reviews,  I just know we absolutely loved this place!

The food was okay tasting, but wasn’t even warm. Our server wasn’t attentive to us, but every time she come by she would keep trying to push more hurricane drinks on us. We had to continuously ask for water. Also, apparently there’s a Chicken Festival going on, so there was an automatic 20% gratuity added to the bill which they didn’t tell us until we asked about it on our bill. Bad service, mediocre food, and not worth the wait or will.

Food was mediocre at best. Worst part was the atmosphere.  Listened to the manager (or owner) berate and belittle the entire staff for our entire meal. He sat right in the middle of the restaurant while doing it, and micro managing all of the employees.  He was very rude to everyone.  Even worse, he was having conversations with some of the employees about the money they owed him right in public as well.  Some very serious conversations that should have been done in private.  Worst meal ever had in New Orleans.
Literally the worst restaurant experience of my life
The owner and other employees go above and beyond for their guests and you can tell they have a real passion for food and for ensuring their guests are happy.

We are a group of 6 people from Colorado that happened upon this restaurant on Saturday night.  We were on our way to another restaurant when Joey stopped us on the sidewalk to give us a rundown of what the menu was all about and to convince us to head inside and give it a try. I am SO HAPPY we decided to eat here.  We were seated immediately and Kathy was our server.  She was sweet and attentive while at the same time joking with our group....named my friend Beth and called her that for the next 2 days when we would walk by.  We ordered drinks and a few appetizers before ordering our entrees.  After we sat down, we immediately struck up a conversation with one of the owners, Frank, and soon had Jack, another owner involved too.  Both guys are awesome and shared story after story with our table.  Now comes the best part....the food!!  Our group ordered a range of food that night. Once we were finished it came time to pay the bill.  There was an 18% gratuity added to the bill, and I was absolutely alright with it.  In an area that is full of tourists and lots of alcohol, I think it's important to protect your servers and employees that work hard for these businesses.  Every restaurant we went to for our trip added a gratuity to our table.  We added more money to the tip each time we visited a restaurant.  Our bill, before the gratuity was added, was about $350.  I found it to be reasonable as we had the majority of our group drinking tasty Hurricanes and we ordered a ton of food.  All in all, this place was amazing!
